Click and hold to add terrain.
Click and hold to erode and remove terrain.
Click and hold to grow and expand terrain.
Paint the material of the terrain.
Brush to smooth out rough or jagged terrain.
Click and hold to remove terrain.
When enabled, air voxels in the selection will overwrite existing voxels at the destination.
Click Upgrade to improve the way water joins with terrain at the shores.

The upgrade will only be applied to this place. This will automatically adjust shallow water shape on existing shorelines. You might want to review and hand-edit the results afterwards, especially around streams, waterfalls and any other non-horizontal water surfaces. The upgrade can be reverted right after its completion using the Undo command.
You can also upgrade this place's shorelines later from the Terrain Editor panel. The upgrade can be reverted right after its completion with the Undo command.
Would you like to upgrade this place's terrain with the new shorelines?
Click Upgrade to make terrain smoother while retaining the current shape.
Note that some baked-in terracing can't be automatically eliminated. Manual edits are needed to achieve the full effect in such areas.
You can find these settings in the Terrain Editor panel.
Would you like to upgrade the terrain with the new smooth look?
Upgrade Shorelines first to enable Smooth Voxels upgrading.
